olive oil
2 potatoes
1 carrot
1 packet flaked almonds
1 packet chicken thigh
1 tsp honey
1 bag baby spinach leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet mayonnaise
1 sachet Mild North Indian Spice Blend
1 sachet Sri Lankan spice blend

• SPICY! The spice blend is mild, but use less if you're sensitive to heat.
• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato and carrot into bite-sized chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle over mild North Indian spice blend, drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper.
• Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 25-30 minutes.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast flaked almonds, tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.
• In a medium bowl, combine chicken thigh, Sri Lankan spice blend, a pinch of salt and a drizzle of olive oil.

• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook chicken until browned, 2 minutes each side.
• Transfer chicken to a second lined oven tray and drizzle with honey. Bake until cooked through, 12-14 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• When the roasted veggies are done, add baby spinach leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar to the tray. Gently toss to combine. Season to taste.
• Slice Sri Lankan-spiced chicken.
• Divide roast veggie toss between plates. Top with chicken.
• Dollop over mayonnaise and garnish with toasted almonds. Enjoy!